Question 2
A “customer id” column in a customer table is expected to include thousands of customers and the data type should be numeric only. What data type should you use to define this column?

1 / 1 point

customerID TINYINT


customerID INT


customerID DECIMAL

Correct
Correct! Integer is a numeric data type that can be used for big whole numbers, which are required here.

